Package: brfssTools
Title: Harmonize Longitudinal BRFSS Survey Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Nathan", "Parsons", , "nathan.f.parsons@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for harmonizing the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance
    System (BRFSS) survey data across years and across sources (national
    CDC LLCP files plus state-collected files), where variable names,
    response codes, and question text drift between waves. Provides a
    'tidycensus'-style workflow built around a user-editable crosswalk:
    initialize a state config, register a pool of raw data files, edit
    the crosswalk via an interactive Shiny GUI, set up declarative
    transformations (YAML categorical maps with year-aware variable
    aliasing) for derived variables like race, and pull harmonized
    concepts as a tidy tibble. State and CDC data live behind a single
    'concept_id' addressing system.
